# =============================================================================
# File: /opt/ansible-k3s-cluster/README.cluster-observability
# =============================================================================
# Purpose:
#   Provide an overview of the observability tooling available in the cluster
#   automation framework. This includes:
#     - Health checks
#     - Kernel diagnostics
#     - Network diagnostics
#     - Storage diagnostics
#     - Power and thermal diagnostics
#
# Observability Components:
#
#   - cluster-health.yml
#   - cluster-service-report.yml
#   - cluster-kernel-report.yml
#   - cluster-dmesg-report.yml
#   - cluster-network-report.yml
#   - cluster-storage-report.yml
#   - cluster-temp-report.yml
#   - cluster-power-report.yml
#   - cluster-filesystem-integrity.yml
#   - cluster-latency-report.yml
#   - cluster-entropy-report.yml
#
# Notes:
#   - Observability is critical for diagnosing distributed build failures.
#   - This file serves as the index for all cluster diagnostics.
# =============================================================================
